item.title: About Us
item.dc:creator: oyenj
item.content:encoded: The mission of Central College Dining Service is to provide superior quality meals and service to our customers, the students, staff, and faculty of the Central College community. We strive to be proactive, responsive, and cooperative in meeting the needs of our customers and internal customers. As we interact with our students on a daily basis we understand the importance of being a positive part of their college experience. We also extend the same level of quality to visitors on campus and strive to make their experience at Central College a memorable one.

item.title: Home
item.dc:creator: oyenj
item.content:encoded: The hearty breakfast that jumpstarts your day. The light lunch that keeps you fresh and focused. The quick snack that helps you reenergize on the go. Or the relaxing dinner you enjoy with friends to celebrate an occasion (or just the end of a long day).   For every meal and any event, Central College Dining Services promises to bring you food that looks, smells and tastes superb. Our three on-campus locations make meals convenient and gratifying for students, staff and faculty, while our full-service catering enriches events around Iowa.

item.title: Meal Plans
item.dc:creator: oyenj
item.content:encoded:
Meal Plans and Pricing

Meal Times Student Guest Employee Child Pricing (8 & Under)
Breakfast $5.00 $5.50 $4.50 $2.75
Lunch $6.00 $7.00 $5.00 $3.50
Dinner $6.50 $7.50 $6.00 $3.75
Sunday Brunch $7.00 $7.50 $7.00 $3.75

Commuter Meal Plan

Living off campus provides students a great sense of independence unfortunately it can also mean provisions are limited to Funyuns, Skittles and Ramen Noodles. But just because you dont live right next to Central Market, doesnt mean you cant still savor the tasty food cooked fresh there every day. The Commuter Meal Plan is specially designed to allow full-time students living off campus the opportunity dine in the Central Market for any 50 meals during the semester. Your Central College ID card will be programmed to keep track of your remaining meals, putting the essence of 50 well-rounded meals in the palm of your hand.

item.title: Catering
item.dc:creator: oyenj
item.content:encoded:
Making the Food that Makes Your Event

 

Catering isnt about dropping off a few metal buffet trays of food and parting ways. Its about preparing amazing food that matches the occasion and wows everyone in attendance. Collectively, our catering team boasts over 100 years of experience. From preparation to presentation we aspire to standards that exceed even those of our customers. Thats why weve garnered a reputation as being one of the premier full-service caterers in Iowa.   Our strengths lie not only in the culinary arts but also in customer service. If you have difficulty selecting from the litany of fantastic options on our menu, well gladly help design a menu that pleases your taste buds and matches your budget. We can also provide the tablecloths and linens that add an extra element of elegance and class to your event. And when it does come time to cook, we promise to use only the best ingredients, including many locally grown items.   We encourage you to spend a few moments perusing our vast menu. From country style breakfasts and box lunches to international themed dinners and decadent desserts, the Central College catering service makes the food that makes your event.

item.title: FAQ
item.dc:creator: oyenj
item.content:encoded:
Catering FAQ

What is Centrals billing policy?

Central requires a 50% deposit for all groups over 100 ten business days prior to the event.Central accepts personal checks as well as credit cards: MasterCard, Visa or Discover.

 

How do I book Centrals Catering?

On Campus Please contact the Conferences and Events Officeto reserve a room then contact the Catering Office 641-628-5788.Off Campus Please contact the Catering Office 641-628-5788 to check on availability

 

How far from Pella does Central cater?

Central will cater within a 60 mile radius from Pella (Des Moines, Knoxville, Oskaloosa, Ottumwa, Monroe, Sully, Lynnville etc.)

item.title: About
item.dc:creator: oyenj
item.content:encoded:
It's About Food. It's About People.

  Comprised of three on-campus dining locations and our renowned catering service, Central College Dining Services is proud to prepare delicious food for students, staff and faculty, as well as a host of companies, institutions and private parties.   An emphasis on quality ingredients, bold flavors and diverse cuisines are why were known across Iowa, while an unwavering commitment to convenience and providing helpful, courteous service is often what our diners and customers appreciate most.   Why the need for three on-campus dining locations? Because each venue features a unique ambiance and offers a selection of food and beverages entirely its own. The Central Market is the center of the Central College Dining Services universe, featuring 12 stations preparing a vast assortment of foods. Grand Central Station is where to enjoy live music and short-order food. And the Caf @ Geisler Library is a cozy coffee shop where you can relax over a cup of fresh java.   Our catering service provides scrumptious catering solutions for corporate events and private parties all across Iowa. With an extensive menu and an experienced, dedicated staff, we make the food that will make your event.

item.title: Policies
item.dc:creator: oyenj
item.content:encoded:
Booking Procedure

The Central College Catering Department is committed to enriching your event with delicious food, delightful presentation and dedicated service. To help us ensure your event is a success, we humbly request that you abide by the following catering policies.  
  • Please reserve your room prior to contacting the Catering Department.
  • Please contact the Catering Department at least 10 business days prior to your event.
  • Be prepared to provide the estimated number of guests at that time and your final guaranteed number three business days prior to the event.
  • Please be aware that should your guaranteed list not be provided by that time, your estimated number will become your guaranteed number, and you will be billed based on the guaranteed or total number served whichever is higher.
  • Cancellation notices must be made no later than four business days prior to the event.
  • In compliance with State of Iowa Regulations, all leftover food is to remain the property ofCentral College.
  Billing Policies
  • We reserve the right to bill for special ordered items we are unable to return.
  • Children ages 4 to 10 are half priced.
  • A 50 percent deposit is required for all groups over 100.
  • Balance paid upon receipt of your bill must be received 10 business days prior to your event.
  • All pricing is subject to change due to seasonal availability and market prices.
  • All Central College groups will be billed through our billing process with your 12-digit budget number.
  • Off campus customers are to contact the Catering Office for additional billing information.

item.title: Central Market
item.dc:creator: oyenj
item.content:encoded:
Central Market

 

In recognition of Central's eight study abroad centers, the Central Market captures the spirit of a European marketplace and serves as the center of the Central College Dining Services universe. Its where good service, good food and good friends meet. The lines are short. The musics lively. And the professional staff is as courteous as can be. Choose from 12 flavorful stations, including Peace Street Pizza, Mongolian Grill, Very Veggie Station, Comfort Foods and Dutch Treats. Theres a pasta station, a Mexican station and a waffle bar, too. Plus cook-to-order Chinese food, omelets and holiday dinners. Want to know the nutrional analysis of what you are eating at the Central Market? Simply click on this link for valuable nutritionalinformation. http://central.mynutritioncalculator.net/

item.title: Fred's
item.dc:creator: oyenj
item.content:encoded:
Fred's

  Theres a cure for every craving and entertainment for all types at Fred's. Juicy burgers. Crispy chicken tenders.Grab andgo items and smoothies.Special events and live concerts. And even some sweet poetry readings for those who feel like getting sentimental over a short-order sandwich. Located on the ground floor of the Maytag Student Center,Fred'sopens early and stays open until11 p.m, 7 days a week. You can get your comfort food fix any time of day, and sit back and watch TV or enjoy socializing with friends, 24 hours a day.

item.title: The Cafe at Geisler
item.dc:creator: oyenj
item.content:encoded:
The Caf @ Geisler Library

 

A cozy coffee house with the sweet aroma of fresh lattes and espressos flavoring the air, wirelessinternet streaming freely and no shortage of comfy furniture waiting to be relaxed in. Gleaming glass cases stacked with fluffy muffins, bagels and scones, fresh salads, fruits and sandwiches. The coffee is organic and of the free trade variety. The perfect place for the focused mind to unwind or recharge. Sounds like Starbucks, right? Yeah, its kind of like Starbucks. Only this library cafe brews with a Central touch.
